# Microsoft Graph MCP Server Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values

# ============================================================================
# Required: Azure AD Configuration
# ============================================================================

# Your Azure AD Tenant ID
# Find this in: Azure Portal > Azure Active Directory > Overview
TENANT_ID=your-tenant-id-here

# Your App Registration Client ID
# Find this in: Azure Portal > App registrations > Your App > Overview
CLIENT_ID=your-client-id-here

# ============================================================================
# Optional: Authentication Configuration
# ============================================================================

# OAuth redirect URI (default: http://localhost:3000/auth/callback)
# Only change if you've configured a different redirect URI in Azure AD
# REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:3000/auth/callback

# Your Microsoft 365 email address (optional, for logging/debugging)
# USER_EMAIL=your-email@domain.com

# ============================================================================
# Optional: Server Configuration
# ============================================================================

# Environment mode (default: development)
# Options: development | production
# NODE_ENV=development

# Logging level (default: info)
# Options: debug | info | warn | error
# LOG_LEVEL=info

# ============================================================================
# Setup Instructions
# ============================================================================
#
# 1. Create an App Registration in Azure AD:
#    - Go to Azure Portal > Azure Active Directory > App registrations
#    - Click "New registration"
#    - Name: "MsGraph-Mcp" (or your preferred name)
#    - Supported account types: Single tenant
#    - Redirect URI: Public client/native > http://localhost:3000/auth/callback
#    - Click "Register"
#
# 2. Configure API Permissions:
#    - In your app registration, go to "API permissions"
#    - Click "Add a permission" > Microsoft Graph > Delegated permissions
#    - Add: Mail.Read, User.Read, offline_access
#    - Click "Grant admin consent" (requires admin rights)
#
# 3. Copy your credentials:
#    - Copy Tenant ID from Azure AD Overview
#    - Copy Client ID from your App Registration Overview
#    - Paste them above
#
# 4. Save this file as .env in the project root
#
# For detailed setup instructions, see: docs/setup/azure-ad-setup.md
# ============================================================================
